# Laravel model: class structure

Use **four** section comments in this **fixed order**. Each section groups related members; do not mix (e.g. do not put relations under `//attr`).

**Spacing:** Do **not** leave a blank line immediately after `//attr`, `//scope`, `//rel`, or `//fun` when that section has members—put the first member on the **next line** directly under the comment.

**Empty `//attr`:** If there are **no** accessors/mutators under `//attr` (nothing whose name includes `Attribute`), **keep one blank line** between `//attr` and `//scope` so the section marker is not flush against the next section.

**Above `//attr`:** After `use ...` traits, list **all configuration** in one block—properties such as **`$fillable`**, **`$casts`**, **`$hidden`**, **`$appends`**, **`$with`**, optional **`protected $table`**, **`$primaryKey`**, **`$guarded`**, and trait config on the model (e.g. **`$translatedAttributes`**). Nothing under the `//attr` comment belongs in this block.

**Under `//attr`:** **Only** members whose **names include `Attribute`**—classic accessors/mutators (`getNameAttribute`, `getImagePathAttribute`, `setFooAttribute`, …) and Laravel **`Attribute::make`** definitions where the method or return type uses **`Attribute`** (e.g. `protected function imagePath(): Attribute`). Do **not** put `$fillable`, `$casts`, or other properties below `//attr`.

| Section   | Contents |
|-----------|----------|
| `//attr`  | **Only** `get*Attribute` / `set*Attribute` and `*(): Attribute` accessors/mutators |
| `//scope` | Query scopes (`scopeWhen*`, `scopeWhenSearch`, …) — name **`scopeWhen{Field}`** without embedding the model class name (see [.cursor/rules/laravel-php-style.mdc](.cursor/rules/laravel-php-style.mdc) **Model query scopes**) |
| `//rel`   | Eloquent relations (`hasMany`, `belongsTo`, …) |
| `//fun`   | Everything else: helpers, **`boot`**, **`getActivitylogOptions`**, route key overrides, other **`Model`** overrides — **not** attribute accessors/mutators |

✔
```php
class Example extends Model
{
    use HasFactory, Translatable;

    protected $fillable = ['name'];

    protected $casts = ['published_at' => 'datetime'];

    protected $hidden = ['internal_only'];

    protected $appends = ['image_path'];

    protected $with = ['translations'];

    public $translatedAttributes = ['title'];

    //attr
    public function getNameAttribute($value): string
    {
        // ...
    }// end of getNameAttribute

    public function getImagePathAttribute(): ?string
    {
        // ...
    }// end of getImagePathAttribute

    //scope
    public function scopeWhenSearch($query, $search)
    {
        // ...
    }// end of scopeWhenSearch

    //rel
    public function company(): BelongsTo
    {
        // ...
    }// end of company

    //fun
    protected static function booted(): void
    {
        // ...
    }// end of booted

} //end of model
```

✔ (no attribute accessors/mutators — blank line after `//attr`)

```php
    //attr

    //scope
    public function scopeWhenSearch($query, $search)
    {
        // ...
    }// end of scopeWhenSearch
```

- Class closing: `} //end of model` (see [.cursor/rules/laravel-php-style.mdc](.cursor/rules/laravel-php-style.mdc)).

